This paper discusses the use of word sense disambiguation and deep learning, which are common topics in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of large datasets for training supervised systems, which is a common topic in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the use of resources such as WordNet and Wikipedia, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and computational linguistics (CY), making cs.IR and cs.CY likely sub-categories as well.
